if MMCSD

config TZSH_MMCSDMINOR
	int "MMC/SD minor number"
	default 0
	---help---
		If board-specific TZSH start-up logic needs to mount an MMC/SD device, then the
		setting should be provided to identify the MMC/SD minor device number (i.e., the N ini
		/dev/mmcsdN).  Default 0

config TZSH_MMCSDSLOTNO
	int "MMC/SD slot number"
	default 0
	---help---
		If board-specific TZSH start-up supports more than one MMC/SD slot, then this setting
		should be provided to indicate which slot should be used.  Default: 0.

config TZSH_MMCSDSPIPORTNO
	int "MMC/SD SPI device number"
	default 0
	depends on MMCSD_SPI
	---help---
		If board-specif TZSH start-up logic will mount an SPI-based MMC/SD volume, then this
		setting may be needed to tell the board logic which SPI bus to use.  Default: 0
		(meaning is board-specific).

endif # MMCSD

menu "Configure Command Options"

config TZSH_VARS
	bool "TZSH variables"
	default n
	---help---
		By default, there are no internal TZSH variables.  TZSH will use OS
		environment variables for all variable storage.  If this option, TZSH
		will also support local TZSH variables.  These variables are, for the
		most part, transparent and work just like the OS environment
		variables.  The difference is that when you create new tasks, all of
		environment variables are inherited by the created tasks.  TZSH local
		variables are not.

		If this option is enabled (and CONFIG_DISABLE_ENVIRON is not), then a
		new command called 'export' is enabled.  The export command works very
		must like the set command except that is operates on environment
		variables.  When CONFIG_TZSH_VARS is enabled, there are changes in the
		behavior of certains commands

		============== =========================== ===========================
		CMD             w/o CONFIG_TZSH_VARS        w/CONFIG_TZSH_VARS
		============== =========================== ===========================
		set <a> <b>    Set environment var a to b  Set TZSH var a to b
		unset <a>      Unsets environment var a    Unsets both environment var
		                                           and TZSH var a
		export <a> <b> Causes an error             Unsets TZSH var a.  Sets
		                                           environment var a to b.
		export <a>     Causes an error             Sets environment var a to
		                                           TZSH var b (or "").  Unsets
		                                           local var a.
		env            Lists all environment       Lists all environment
		               variables                   variables
		============== =========================== ===========================

config TZSH_CMDOPT_DD_STATS
	bool "dd: Support transfer statistics"
	default n
	depends on !TZSH_DISABLE_DD

config TZSH_CODECS_BUFSIZE
	int "File buffer size used by CODEC commands"
	default 128

